\section{Fabrication}
Samples were fabricated starting from silicon‑-on‑-insulator (SOI) wafers with 220nm Si thickness. On top of the Si layer, a 100nm--thick layer of silicon--rich silica ($ SiO_x $) was grown by PECVD, and annealed at 1000$^o$C in $ N_2 $ ambient for 210s. The amount of silicon excess was 16\% and Silicon-nanocrystals had an an average size of 4nm . On top of that layer, a 240nm-thick layer of amorphous $ Si $ was grown by Plasma-enhanced chemical vapor deposition (PECVD) to form the top half of the waveguide. Waveguides were patterned with deep-UV lithography and etched down to the buried oxide to form channels as the ones reported in \cite{Martinez2010a, Trita2011}. The whole layout was covered with silica after the etching process. On the other hand, Si strip waveguides were also fabricated for comparison. These were also processed from SOI wafers patterned wtih deep-UV lithography, and their dimensions were 445x220 for TE polarization and 485x220 for TM polarization. TE waveguide was 10mm long and TM 25mm.

%Samples had the same fabrication as the one in paper \cite{Trita2011}, manufactured during the European project PHOLOGIC.

